(2973, 1, '2015-09-03 05:42:51', '2015-09-03 05:42:51', '', 'Learn to Read Quran Fluently', 'Learning how to recite the Quran is now easier than ever! Learn Quran provides comprehensive lessons ranging from very basic topics (The Alphabet, Harakaat, etc.) to advanced Tajweed lessons, making this app suitable for learners at all levels.\r\n\r\nLearn Quran is designed so you can learn with a teacher or by yourself. It''s your Quran learning guide.\r\n\r\nCONTENTS:\r\n1. THEORY: Learn the topic using words taken from the Quran.\r\n2. PRACTICE: Master the topic by practicing what you’ve learned (using Quranic examples).\r\n3. TEST: Measure your comprehension by testing what you’ve learned (again based on words from the Quran).\r\n\r\nFEATURES:\r\n• VOICE: Voice narration of the Arabic words, making learning simple.\r\n• TRANSLITERATION (can be turned on/off): Transliteration of the Arabic text, making reading easy. The transliterations are based on UNESCO\r\n• RECORDING: Voice recording to allow you to compare your recitation to the voice-over, making it easy to measure how much you’ve learnt.\r\n\r\nLearn Quran features Haafiz Muhammad S. Bashir as the voice-over. He is the first winner of the International Competition on Quran (Kuwait, 2014) and a teacher of various Quran classes. We want you to learn from the best.\r\n\r\nDISCLAIMER\r\nOur reason for locking some of the content in the free version: We hire professional developers (whose services are expensive) and our resources are limited. We apologize for our limitations. Please make dua that one day Allah enables us to provide Islamic applications for free.\r\n\r\nP.S. If you find any errors, the best way to give feedback is by sending an email (as opposed to writing a review). This guarantees your feedback will reach the right person inshaaAllah.\r\n\r\nCP: <a href="mailto:sani@badr-interactive.com">sani@badr-interactive.com</a>', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'learn-to-read-quran-fluently', '', '', '2015-09-04 08:37:32', '2015-09-04 08:37:32', '', 0, 'http://localhost/badr/?post_type=project&#038;p=2973', 0, 'project', '', 0),
(2974, 1, '2015-09-03 06:01:28', '2015-09-03 06:01:28', '', 'Toyota - Teman Mudik Lebaran', 'TOYOTA TEMAN MUDIK LEBARAN merupakan aplikasi yang dibangun oleh PT.Toyota-Astra Motor yang bertujuan untuk memberikan kenyamanan bagi pengguna TOYOTA tidak hanya bagi orang tua tapi juga bagi anggota keluarga lainnya.\r\n\r\nAplikasi ini dilengkapi dengan games dan musik yang menarik, diharapkan dapat menambah kenyamanan dalam berkendara.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'toyota-teman-mudik-lebaran', '', '', '2015-09-04 08:36:48', '2015-09-04 08:36:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost/badr/?post_type=project&#038;p=2974', 0, 'project', '', 0),
(2975, 1, '2015-09-03 06:05:31', '2015-09-03 06:05:31', '', 'Quran Prize', 'Quran Prize is about using information technology to serve three purposes, i.e to encourage, appreciate and appraise people to master the Quran. It starts with reading and memorizing assessment, but insha Allah will be also developed into understanding, Quranic based – problem solving and even up to exercising the Quran teaching and values into daily live.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'quran-prize', '', '', '2015-09-04 08:37:19', '2015-09-04 08:37:19', '', 0, 'http://localhost/badr/?post_type=project&#038;p=2975', 0, 'project', '', 0),
(2976, 1, '2015-09-03 06:06:40', '2015-09-03 06:06:40', '', 'Masjeed', 'Masjeed is a mosque-based social network. Masjeed presents a new experience in interacting with the mosques and its activities.\r\n\r\nMasjeed connects people with the mosques, allowing them to engage each other regarding the activities of the mosques. “Who will be giving the Jum’ah lecture in my area?”, “What events the mosque held this weekend?”, “Where do I want to go for I''tikaf this Ramadhan?”, the beautiful community of the mosques will help each other, care and know more about their mosques, or work together to make their mosques even more productive and impactful.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'masjeed', '', '', '2015-09-04 08:11:51', '2015-09-04 08:11:51', '', 0, 'http://localhost/badr/?post_type=project&#038;p=2976', 0, 'project', '', 0),
(2979, 1, '2015-09-06 16:31:17', '2015-09-06 16:31:17', '[gravityform id="1" title="true" description="true" ajax="true"]\r\n\r\nIn <a title="Publishing" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Publishing">publishing</a> and <a title="Graphic design" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphic_design">graphic design</a>, <b>lorem ipsum</b> (derived from Latin <i>dolorem ipsum</i>, translated as "pain itself") is a <a title="Filler text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Filler_text">filler text</a>commonly used to demonstrate the <a class="mw-redirect" title="Graphic" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphic">graphic</a> elements of a document or visual presentation. Replacing meaningful content with placeholder text allows viewers to focus on graphic aspects such as <a title="Font" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Font">font</a>, <a title="Typography" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Typography">typography</a>, and <a title="Page layout" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Page_layout">page layout</a> without being distracted by the content. It also reduces the need for the designer to come up with meaningful text, as they can instead use quickly-generated lorem ipsum.\r\n\r\nThe lorem ipsum text is typically a scrambled section of <i><a title="De finibus bonorum et malorum" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/De_finibus_bonorum_et_malorum">De finibus bonorum et malorum</a></i>, a 1st-century BC <a title="Latin" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin">Latin</a> text by<a title="Cicero" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cicero">Cicero</a>, with words altered, added, and removed to make it nonsensical, improper Latin.\r\n\r\nA variation of the ordinary lorem ipsum text has been used in <a title="Typesetting" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Typesetting">typesetting</a> since the 1960s or earlier, when it was popularized by advertisements for <a title="Letraset" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Letraset">Letraset</a> transfer sheets. It was introduce